  "doc_id": "26890",
  "text": "Passive valves include capillary valves, hydrophobic valves, and siphon valves [CITATION_1] . These types of valves are controlled primarily by the rotational frequency, surface properties, and channel design of the disc. Johnson et al. [CITATION_2] used capillary valves for the sequential handling of fluids. Siegrist et al. [CITATION_3] developed a more integrated system by implementing a robust serial siphoning method of fluid handling. This system was advanced further by integrating the serial siphoning system with a heterogeneous sandwich immunoassay and surface-confined supercritical angle fluorescence (SAF) detection of human immunoglobulin G (hIgG) [CITATION_4] . Godino et al.",
